{
    "attributes": {
        "action": "Introduce Automatic Wage Indexation and cap income tax",
        "additional_details": "In some countries like Belgium and Luxemburg, governments mandate that wages must increase automatically when certain prices go up using a pivot index (PC 200) which adjusts every January. We think this will mean salaries will match cost-of-living and less burden on workforce to make ends meet.",
        "background": "Inflation is increasing far more rapidly than competitive salary ranges. In the last 10 years, average UK salaries have stagnated and many are not competitive globally. With the cost-of-living crisis, salaries must be increased and income tax must be capped to improve affordability of living.",
